From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000001 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: solarizeddev <info@solarized.dev>
Date: Thu, 1 Jan 1970 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] ffmpeg-android-maker: hook Firedown patch application

After all components have been downloaded but before any per-ABI build
loops start, invoke firedown/apply-firedown-patches.sh to apply
Firedown's modifications (replacement http.c, hls.c patch, and configure
edits) to the freshly-extracted FFmpeg source tree.

Running once before the build loop means the patches are applied a
single time and benefit every ABI build that follows.

The hook is conditional on the apply script being executable and present,
so this modification is a no-op for upstream/non-Firedown builds.

---
 ffmpeg-android-maker.sh | 10 ++++++++++
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+)

--- a/ffmpeg-android-maker.sh
+++ b/ffmpeg-android-maker.sh
@@ -94,6 +94,16 @@
   cd ${BASE_DIR}
 done
 
+# === Firedown: apply project-specific patches to FFmpeg source ===
+# After all components have been downloaded but before any builds start,
+# apply Firedown's modifications to the FFmpeg source tree. This runs once
+# and benefits all subsequent per-ABI builds.
+if [[ -x "${BASE_DIR}/firedown/apply-firedown-patches.sh" ]]; then
+  echo "Applying Firedown patches to FFmpeg source..."
+  "${BASE_DIR}/firedown/apply-firedown-patches.sh" "${SOURCES_DIR_ffmpeg}" || exit 1
+fi
+# === End Firedown patches ===
+
 # Main build loop
 for ABI in ${FFMPEG_ABIS_TO_BUILD[@]}
 do
